<!--
    Mg-1.1 DI override.

    Maps Magento\InventoryDistanceBasedSourceSelectionApi\Api\GetLatsLngsFromAddressInterface
    to our no-op stub.

    Upstream Magento OSS 2.4.6-p10 / 2.4.7-p3 wire this interface to the
    real GetLatsLngsFromAddress concrete (in the InventoryDistanceBasedSourceSelection
    module, NOT the Api module), which in turn depends on
    GetGeoCodesForAddress whose ctor declares ClientInterface but DI hands
    it Curl - PHP strict typing throws. The error surfaces as:

        Cannot instantiate interface
        Magento\InventoryDistanceBasedSourceSelectionApi\Api\GetLatsLngsFromAddressInterface

    ...when ObjectManager tries to walk the resolution chain at
    $quote->collectTotals() time.

    The no-op stub returns an empty lat/lng list, which is a legal
    "no geocoding data available" response per the interface contract.
    Our OST tax-calculation plugin doesn't touch MSI source-selection
    at all, so this short-circuit is loss-less for the Mg-1 assertion.

    Because module.xml declares <sequence>Magento_InventoryDistanceBasedSourceSelectionApi</sequence>
    this di.xml loads AFTER the upstream Api module's di.xml, so our
    preference wins via Magento's standard last-write-wins DI merge.
-->
<config xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
        xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:magento:framework:ObjectManager/etc/config.xsd">
    <preference for="Magento\InventoryDistanceBasedSourceSelectionApi\Api\GetLatsLngsFromAddressInterface"
                type="EJOsterberg\OstaxTestStubs\Stubs\GetLatsLngsFromAddressInterfaceStub"/>
</config>
